WEBVTT

00:00:00.320 --> 00:00:04.880
Hi, I'm Rich. I'd like to publish a data table on Quarto.Pub that I can share with the world.

00:00:05.600 --> 00:00:08.000
Great, so let's make a new Quarto document.

00:00:08.640 --> 00:00:12.400
And what we get is a Quarto document which is filled out with some boilerplate.

00:00:14.160 --> 00:00:18.080
I'm going to switch my editor from visual to source mode and edit the file directly.

00:00:18.959 --> 00:00:21.920
I'd like to share a table pulled from the gt pack as examples.

00:00:22.719 --> 00:00:24.160
I'm going to use that in this code chunk.

00:00:25.200 --> 00:00:26.400
I'm going to save this now.

00:00:27.120 --> 00:00:30.240
Just to check that it looks good, I'm going to render this.

00:00:30.240 --> 00:00:31.600
I have Quarto installed.

00:00:31.600 --> 00:00:36.080
I went to Quarto.org and got the installation file for that.

00:00:37.200 --> 00:00:42.160
Great, and now this renders as a Quarto document and it looks really good.

00:00:42.160 --> 00:00:44.880
It's going up and down and I'm quite satisfied with this table.

00:00:45.919 --> 00:00:49.840
Now the next step, I'm going to publish this inside of Quarto.Pub.

00:00:49.840 --> 00:00:51.520
So we don't do that in the console.

00:00:51.520 --> 00:00:52.560
We go to Terminal.

00:00:53.279 --> 00:00:58.880
And because we have the Quarto CLI installed, I'm just going to type in Quarto and publish.

00:01:01.200 --> 00:01:03.919
And now what it does is it shows you a list of providers.

00:01:03.919 --> 00:01:05.680
But what we want is Quarto.Pub.

00:01:05.680 --> 00:01:07.040
So I'm going to hit enter on that.

00:01:08.559 --> 00:01:09.919
It's going to ask you to authorize.

00:01:10.639 --> 00:01:12.320
I'm going to hit capital Y.

00:01:14.879 --> 00:01:17.360
And now we're brought to the Quarto sign-in page.

00:01:17.919 --> 00:01:18.720
I have an account.

00:01:18.720 --> 00:01:21.199
If you don't, sign up right here at the bottom.

00:01:22.080 --> 00:01:24.000
But I have a sign-in through GitHub.

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:25.040
So I'm going to click on that.

00:01:26.239 --> 00:01:28.320
And as we can see here, it just takes me right in.

00:01:29.040 --> 00:01:30.480
And it asks me to authorize.

00:01:30.480 --> 00:01:31.199
I will allow this.

00:01:32.720 --> 00:01:34.080
And now we can close this window.

00:01:34.080 --> 00:01:36.959
And now it's asking me for the name of the document.

00:01:36.959 --> 00:01:37.919
I'm satisfied with that.

00:01:37.919 --> 00:01:38.959
I'm going to hit enter.

00:01:41.120 --> 00:01:44.239
And right now it's going to publish that through the usual way.

00:01:44.239 --> 00:01:47.360
And it's going to show you some additional information about what it's doing when it's

00:01:47.360 --> 00:01:48.080
publishing.

00:01:48.080 --> 00:01:49.120
This doesn't take very long.

00:01:49.839 --> 00:01:52.239
And it just creates the site, publishes it.

00:01:53.040 --> 00:01:56.559
And you are now in the admin's view of my published table on Quarto.pub.

00:01:57.120 --> 00:01:58.239
It's showing you your table.

00:01:59.199 --> 00:02:00.720
And it's giving you some controls.

00:02:00.720 --> 00:02:01.919
It's telling you where it's published at.

00:02:01.919 --> 00:02:06.239
This is actually the link you need for the entry for the table contest.

00:02:06.239 --> 00:02:07.120
I'm going to click on this.

00:02:07.839 --> 00:02:09.199
And this is what other people will see.

00:02:09.199 --> 00:02:10.800
They'll see this exact page.

00:02:10.800 --> 00:02:15.440
And you'll just need to copy this and use that when you make your entry.

00:02:16.399 --> 00:02:17.759
And it's as simple as that.

00:02:17.759 --> 00:02:20.720
We've created and published a table to Quarto.pub.

00:02:20.720 --> 00:02:22.240
Can't wait to see what you create.

